    %hr
    %h5 Disclosure of your Personal Data
    %p We reserve the right to disclose your Personal Data as required by law within the meaning of section 6.1 (c) GDPR, and when we believe that disclosure is necessary to protect our rights; to comply with a judicial proceeding, court order, or legal process served on us or the Website; or in connection with an actual or proposed corporate transaction or insolvency proceeding involving all or part of the business or asset to which the information pertains.
    %p We may disclose your Personal Data if we are so requested by the law, government agencies or statutory bodies within the European Union, to the extent permitted by GDPR. In particular, we may disclose Personal Data in response to a court order or a subpoena. We may also disclose Personal Data to a law enforcement agency’s request or where we believe it is necessary to prevent, investigate or take action regarding illegal activities or suspected fraud. We may use Personal Data to enforce Askdemos’s rights to resolve claims and disputes, to prevent or take action regarding a breach or intended breach of our Terms of Service, to protect other users, to investigate complaints and to prevent unlawful use of the Askdemos Website and Services.
    %p In the event of a reorganization, merger or acquisition, we may transfer any and all of your Personal Data to the relevant buyer or third party as part of the transaction, provided that the conditions of this Privacy Policy would continue to apply.
    %hr
    %h5 Right to access to your Personal Data (section 15 GDPR)
    %p You have the right to access your Personal Data processed by Askdemos (section 15 GDPR). The exercise of the right to access and receive a copy of your data is free if you exercise it under reasonable conditions. In addition to a complete copy of your Personal Data, Askdemos will also provide you with the complete list of information provided for in section 13 of the GDPR. If your requests are manifestly unfounded or excessive, in particular because of their repeated nature, Askdemos may either refuse to answer you or charge you for the provision of this information.
    %p You may exercise your right to access your Personal Data by email sent to Askdemos or by clicking on this link.
    %hr
    %h5 Right to rectification (section 16 GDPR)
    %p You can at any time ask Askdemos to rectify, as soon as possible, your Personal Data if this data is inaccurate.
    %p You may exercise your right to rectify your Personal Data by email sent to Askdemos or by clicking on this link to access to your User‘s account, so that you can rectify yourself any Personal Data that you deem inaccurate.
    %hr
    %h5 Transparency requirement
    %p If Askdemos does not take action when you exercise your right to access or rectify, Askdemos will inform you without delay and, at the latest, within one month of receipt of your request, of the reasons for not taking action and of the possibility of lodging a complaint with the relevant supervisory authority of your EU country and seeking a judicial remedy.
    %hr
    %h5 Security
    %p Askdemos implements appropriate technical and organisational measures to ensure your Personal Data are adequately protected. Please refer to our Security page here here.
    %p We do not knowingly collect Personal Information from children under the age of 13. If we become aware that a child under the age of 13 has provided us with Personal Information, we will take steps to remove that information and terminate the applicable account.
    %li Safeguarding login information
    %p You are responsible for safeguarding your login credentials such as your username and password combination. Make sure your computer is protected with appropriate antivirus software that includes anti-malware software and make sure you are running up-to-date versions and continually getting updates. Treat your mobile device just like you would your computer.
    %p If you notice suspicious account activity, or if your computer or mobile device is lost or stolen and you believe there is a reasonable chance of misuse of your Askdemos login credentials, please contact us immediately at support@askdemos.com.
    %p If you have any questions about security on our Website, you can e-mail us at security@askdemos.com.
    %li Notification of Personal Data Breach
    %p “Personal Data Breach” means a breach of security leading to the accidental or unlawful destruction, loss, alteration, unauthorized disclosure of, or access to, Personal Data transmitted, stored or otherwise processed by Askdemos.
    %p In case of breach of your Personal Data, Askdemos shall notify such data breach without delay to the relevant Supervisory Authority in the EU. In addition, when the Personal Data breach is likely to result in a high risk to the rights and freedoms of its EU Customers, Askdemos shall inform you of the Personal Data breach without undue delay.
    %hr
    %h5 Changes to our Privacy Policy
    %p If we decide to change our Privacy Policy, we will post changes to this Privacy Policy on the Website and other places we deem appropriate so that you are aware of what information we collect, why the information is collected, how the information is used, and under what circumstances, if any, the information is disclosed. Askdemos may require your prior acceptance of the new version of such Privacy Policy. If you disagree with any revisions or updates of this Privacy Policy, you must immediately terminate your registration with this Website and discontinue your use of this Website and Services.
    %hr
    %h5 Your Consent
    %p By using the Website, you consent to the current version of our Privacy Policy.
    %hr
    %h5 Changes to our Privacy Policy
    %p If we decide to change our Privacy Policy, we will post changes to this Privacy Policy on the Website and other places we deem appropriate so that you are aware of what information we collect, why the information is collected, how the information is used, and under what circumstances, if any, the information is disclosed. Your continued used of the Services after any changes or revisions to this Privacy Policy shall indicate your agreement and consent with the terms of such revised Privacy Policy. If you disagree with any revisions or updates of this Privacy Policy, you must immediately terminate your registration with this Website and discontinue your use of this Website and Services.
